statement.p:
Let A=\mat{0 0 -1;0 1 0;-1 0 -1}
Find the determinant of A.
Find the volume of the parallelepiped defined by the columns of A.

ol.li:
After the first row swap above, the matrix becomes upper-triangular:
                        \mat{-1 0 -1;0 1 0;0 0 -1}
                        Hence the determinant of A is -(-1) \cdot 1 \cdot (-1) = -1.
